olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 bunch chives
1 lemon
2 tomato
1 packet sour cream
1 packet garlic aioli
1 bag salad leaves

Boil a kettle of water. Cut the potato into bite-sized chunks. Place the potato
in large saucepan, cover with the boiling water and cook over a high heat until
easily pierced with a knife, 10-12 minutes. Drain, return to the pan, toss with
the chicken-style stock powder and set aside to cool.

While the potato is cooking, roughly chop the mild chorizo. In a medium
frying pan, heat a small drizzle of olive oil over a high heat. Cook the chorizo,
tossing, until golden, 4-6 minutes. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel
and allow to cool.

While the chorizo is cooking, finely chop the chives. Slice the lemon into
wedges. Roughly chop the tomato. In a small bowl, combine the chives, sour
cream, garlic aioli and a squeeze of lemon. Season with salt and pepper.

When you're ready to pack lunch, divide the dressing between two reusable
containers. Top with the cooled chorizo and potato. Top with the tomato,
spinach & rocket mix and any remaining lemon wedges. At lunchtime, toss
the creamy potato and chorizo salad.